      "content": "Nationalism is a deeply complex ideology, and its impact is rarely black and white. When it fosters shared culture, identity, and civic pride, it can be a powerful unifying force for a society. However, when it morphs into extreme chauvinism, it becomes a dangerous tool that justifies exclusion, conflict, and aggression against \"others.\" Therefore, whether it is inherently bad depends entirely on how it is practiced and utilized.",
